# Dashboard Home (`/dashboard`)

`ui/dashboard/index.html` + `ui/src/pages/dashboard-home.ts`

The dashboard home is the **only** application list page. `/dashboard/history` was permanently removed — do not re-add it. All filtering, sorting, searching, and bulk operations live here.

---

## API — `GET /api/v1/applications/`

| Param | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `search` | `str` (max 200) | Case-insensitive `LIKE` across `job_title` AND `company_name` (`OR`). Takes priority over `company`. |
| `status_filter` | `str` | Case-insensitive status match. Values: `PROCESSING`, `COMPLETED`, `APPLIED`, `INTERVIEW`, `REJECTED`, `ACCEPTED`. |
| `days` | `int` (1–365) | Filter by last N days (based on `created_at`). |
| `sort` | `str` | `created_desc` (default) \| `created_asc` \| `updated_desc` \| `company_asc` \| `title_asc` |
| `page` | `int` (≥1) | Page number (1-indexed). |
| `per_page` | `int` (1–100) | Results per page (default 20). |
| `company` | `str` (max 200) | Legacy company-name filter; ignored when `search` is also present. |

The backend uses `func.lower().contains()` (parameterised — no SQL injection risk). Unknown `sort` values silently fall back to `created_desc`.

### List + stats visibility (`_dashboard_application_visibility_filter`)

`GET /api/v1/applications/` and `GET /api/v1/applications/stats/overview` **outerjoin** `workflow_sessions` on `job_applications.session_id` and exclude rows where `workflow_sessions.workflow_status = 'failed'` (in addition to `deleted_at IS NULL` and `job_applications.status != 'failed'`).

**Why:** `job_applications` can remain `processing` for a short window after the workflow session is already `failed`, while `_format_application_response()` maps that pair to a **failed** badge for the API consumer — which used to show a phantom FAILED card. Filtering on workflow status keeps failed analyses off the list and aligns counts with the empty state. See **`applypilot-core.mdc`** (workflow failure — no partial client data).

### Stats overview (`GET /api/v1/applications/stats/overview`)

Rendered in `#statsCards` on the dashboard home page. Uses the same visibility filter as the list (excludes workflow-failed rows).

| Card | Count logic |
|---|---|
| **Total Applications** | All visible (non-deleted, non-workflow-failed) rows |
| **Applied** | Rows in **any** user tracking stage: `applied`, `interview`, `accepted` (Offer), or `rejected` — not “Applied-only” |
| **Interviews** | Rows with status `interview` |
| **Response Rate** | **Numerator:** `interview` + `accepted` + `rejected` (employer-side outcomes). **Denominator:** `applied` + `interview` + `accepted` + `rejected`. Analysis-only rows (no tracking stage) are **excluded** from both. **Applied** is in the denominator but **not** the numerator. |

Do not revert to counting all list rows in the response-rate denominator — that diluted the metric with analysis-only cards.

### List pagination — no duplicate rows on Load More

`api/applications.py` list query uses **`EXISTS`** for workflow-session visibility (not a bare **`LEFT JOIN`** that duplicated rows under **`OFFSET`**). Stable **`ORDER BY`** includes an **`id`** tie-breaker. **`ui/src/pages/dashboard-home.ts`** also dedupes merged pages by application **`id`** when appending Load More results.

