## JS State (`ui/src/pages/dashboard-home.ts`)

All state is module-scoped inside the IIFE:

| Variable | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `_loadedApps` | All applications currently rendered (may span multiple pages) |
| `_totalCount` | Total matching count from last API response |
| `_nextPage` | Next page to fetch for "Load more" |
| `_isLoading` | True while a load sequence is running |
| `_pendingLoadApplicationsReset` | If a **reset** refresh was requested while loading, run another full pass when the current run finishes (WebSocket races) |
| `_loadApplicationsInFlight` | `Promise` for the active `loadApplications` run — concurrent callers **await** this instead of returning early with no refresh |
| `_selected` | `Set<string>` of selected application IDs |
| `_search`, `_status`, `_days`, `_sort` | Current active filter values |
| `_searchTimer` | Debounce timer ID for search input (300 ms) |

Session storage key: `'dash_filter_state'` — persists `search`, `status`, `days`, `sort`, `scrollY` across navigation (back button).

