## HTML Structure

Each card uses a **2-column layout**: left column (title, company, meta) and right column (AI badge top, tracking buttons + trash bottom).

```
#applicationsList  (role="list")
  └─ .application-card.border-status-{status}  (data-card-id="{detailId}")
       └─ .card-layout
            ├─ .card-left
            │    ├─ h6.application-title
            │    ├─ .company-name
            │    └─ .application-meta
            │         ├─ <span title="{absDate}"> relative timestamp
            │         └─ match score (optional)
            └─ .card-right
                 ├─ .card-right-top
                 │    ├─ .follow-up-badge  (shown when applied + stale ≥ 14 days)
                 │    └─ .card-ai-badge.ai-{processing|ready|failed|draft}  (read-only)
                 └─ .card-right-bottom
                      ├─ .card-tracking-row  (only when analysis complete)
                      │    ├─ button.track-btn.track-applied   (data-action="set-tracking" data-value="applied")
                      │    ├─ button.track-btn.track-interview (data-action="set-tracking" data-value="interview")
                      │    ├─ button.track-btn.track-accepted  (data-action="set-tracking" data-value="accepted")
                      │    └─ button.track-btn.track-rejected  (data-action="set-tracking" data-value="rejected")
                      └─ button.card-delete-btn  (data-action="delete" data-id)
```

### AI Analysis Badge vs. Tracking Stage Buttons

These are **two separate concepts** — never combine them:

| Concept | Where | What it shows |
|---|---|---|
| **AI analysis badge** (read-only) | top-right `.card-right-top` | `Analyzing…` (blue spinner), `✓ Ready` (cyan), `Failed` (red), `Draft` (gray) |
| **Tracking stage buttons** (user-editable) | bottom-right `.card-right-bottom` | `Applied` / `Interview` / `Offer` / `Rejected` — only shown when analysis is complete |

The AI badge reflects the backend workflow state. Tracking buttons let the user record where they are in the job process. The two are independent.

**Toggle behaviour:** Clicking an already-active tracking button resets the status back to `completed` (untracked). The success message is:
- Activating a stage → `"Marked as Applied."` / `"Marked as Interview."` etc.
- Deactivating (toggle off) → `"Stage cleared."` — **never** `"Status updated to Completed."`

