## Event Delegation Pattern

All interactive elements use `data-action` — **no inline `onclick`/`onchange`**.

```javascript
// Static elements → document-level listener
document.addEventListener('click', e => {
    const el = e.target.closest('[data-action]');
    switch (el?.dataset.action) {
        case 'load-more':   loadApplications(false); break;
        case 'bulk-delete': bulkDelete(); break;
        case 'logout':      logout(); break;
    }
});

// Dynamic card elements → #applicationsList listener
list.addEventListener('click', e => {
    // e.stopPropagation on input prevents card navigation
    // data-action="delete"      → deleteApplication(id)
    // data-action="set-tracking" → updateApplicationStatus(id, value | 'completed' if already active)
    // card body click (no action) → viewApplication(cardId)
});
list.addEventListener('change', e => {
    // data-action="toggle-select" → toggles _selected Set
});
```

### Tracking button toggle logic

```javascript
// In the set-tracking click handler:
const chosen = actionEl.dataset['value'];
const app = _loadedApps.find(a => String(a['id']) === id);
const currentStatus = app ? String(app['status']).toLowerCase() : '';
// Clicking the already-active button deactivates it
updateApplicationStatus(id, currentStatus === chosen ? 'completed' : chosen);
```

