## Authentication Guard

Two-layer gate — both must pass before the dashboard renders content:

1. **`checkAuthentication()`** — checks the auth token AND `localStorage.getItem('profile_completed') !== 'true'`; if either fails, immediately redirects to `/auth/login` or `/profile/setup` respectively.
2. **`loadUserData()` (authoritative server-side check)** — calls `GET /api/v1/profile/` and checks `data.completion_status?.profile_completed`; if `false`, executes `window.location.href = '/profile/setup'; return;` immediately — **never just shows a banner**. This is the hard gate that prevents users with incomplete profiles from accessing the dashboard even if localStorage is stale.

```javascript
// ✅ Correct — hard redirect, stop all further rendering
if (!data.completion_status?.profile_completed) {
    window.location.href = '/profile/setup';
    return;
}

// ❌ Wrong — soft banner, user can still see broken dashboard
if (!data.completion_status?.profile_completed) {
    document.getElementById('profileCompletionBanner')?.classList.remove('d-none');
}
```

The hard gate is required because the Chrome extension and all API endpoints fail or return 403 for incomplete profiles, so a soft banner just leaves users on a broken page.

