## Cross-Page Navbar Notification Badge (`ui/src/pages/navbar-notifications.ts`)

`ui/src/pages/navbar-notifications.ts` is loaded globally in `base.html`. It shows a small pulsing cyan dot on the "← Back to Dashboard" button in `navbar_subpage.html` when an analysis completes while the user is on a subpage (Career Tools, New Application, etc.).

### localStorage keys
| Key | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `applypilot_tracked_sessions` | `[{sessionId}]` — sessions to watch; added by `ui/src/pages/dashboard-new-application.ts` on submit |
| `applypilot_badge` | `'1'` when a completed analysis hasn't been toasted yet on the dashboard |
| `applypilot_notified_analyses` | JSON array of keys: **`c:{sessionId}`** / **`f:{sessionId}`** (plus legacy bare `sessionId` = completion only). Managed by `ui/src/pages/dashboard-home.ts`; **`ui/src/pages/navbar-notifications.ts`** treats bare, `c:`, and `f:` as “already notified” for the badge |

### Behaviour
- **On subpages**: opens the same `/api/v1/ws/user` WebSocket as `ui/src/pages/dashboard-home.ts`; on `workflow_complete` / `workflow_error` sets `applypilot_badge = '1'` and shows the dot
- **One-shot load check**: on page load, checks any tracked sessions once (catches completions while browser was closed)
- **On `/dashboard`**: clears `applypilot_badge` immediately and exits — `ui/src/pages/dashboard-home.ts` owns all toasts there
- **`window.clearNavBadge()`**: exposed function; called by `ui/src/pages/dashboard-home.ts` `DOMContentLoaded` to clear the dot when user arrives on the dashboard

### Adding the session to tracked list (in `ui/src/pages/dashboard-new-application.ts`)
```javascript
const parsed = JSON.parse(responseText);
const sessionId = parsed && parsed.session_id;
if (sessionId) {
    const raw = localStorage.getItem('applypilot_tracked_sessions') || '[]';
    const tracked = JSON.parse(raw);
    tracked.push({ sessionId });
    if (tracked.length > 20) tracked.splice(0, tracked.length - 20);
    localStorage.setItem('applypilot_tracked_sessions', JSON.stringify(tracked));
}
```

