## Non-Negotiables

1. **Never re-add `/dashboard/history`** — the route is deleted; all application listing is on `/dashboard`
2. **All user data through `escapeHtml()`** in `renderCard()` — job titles and company names may contain HTML entities (`&amp;`, `&#x27;`) from the backend sanitizer; `escapeHtml()` in `ui/src/pages/dashboard-home.ts` must use the decode-first pattern (decode `&amp;` → `&` FIRST, then named entities, then re-encode) to avoid rendering `&amp;` literally in card titles. See `frontend-js-strict.mdc` §1.
3. **`window.showConfirm()`** for all destructive actions (delete, bulk-delete) — never `confirm()`
4. **`saveFilterState()`** before any navigation (`viewApplication()`, etc.) so the browser back button restores the same filters and scroll position
5. **No `style="..."` in `renderCard()` output** — use CSS classes; inline styles are blocked by CSP `style-src`
6. **`updateApplicationStatus()` updates in-memory state** before re-rendering so the UI is responsive without a full reload
7. **Bulk delete uses `Promise.all`** — parallel requests, not sequential
8. **`loadUserData()` must hard-redirect to `/profile/setup` when `profile_completed` is false** — `window.location.href = '/profile/setup'; return;` with an immediate `return` to stop all further rendering; never replace this with a banner or toast
9. **All dashboard section-header CSS goes in `app.css`, never in an inline `<style>` block** — the CSP `style-src` nonce-based policy means inline `<style>` blocks without a correct server-issued nonce are silently ignored by the browser; external stylesheet rules always apply
10. **The empty state is always "No applications yet"** — do not show a different message or icon when filters are active; the user can already see which filters are set in the dropdowns; a single consistent empty state is simpler and less noisy
11. **No "Filtered" badge and no "×" clear button in the header** — the dropdowns themselves communicate which filters are active; extra indicators are redundant UI noise
12. **Never use Bootstrap `form-control-sm` / `form-select-sm` on dashboard filter inputs**
13. **Never use a `<select>` for inline card status** — the status dropdown was replaced with a read-only AI badge + explicit tracking stage buttons; do not restore the dropdown
14. **The status filter only shows tracking stages** (Applied, Interview, Offer, Rejected) — never add Processing or Completed back to `#statusFilter`
15. **Clicking an active tracking button must toggle it off** (reset to `completed`), not re-save the same status — the success toast must say `"Stage cleared."` not `"Status updated to Completed."`
16. **`window.clearNavBadge()` must be called in `ui/src/pages/dashboard-home.ts` DOMContentLoaded** before showing toasts — it clears the navbar dot that was set on subpages while the user was away from the dashboard
17. **`handleUserWsMessage` must handle `agent_update` for new sessions** — if `type === 'agent_update'` and the session is NOT in `_loadedApps`, call `loadApplications(true)` immediately so extension-submitted jobs appear on the dashboard without a manual refresh
18. **`handleUserWsMessage` must not pre-call `_markAnalysisNotified` before `await loadApplications(true)` on `workflow_complete` / `workflow_error`** — that blocked `notifyReady` from ever showing. **`notifyReady()`** performs `_markAnalysisNotified(detailId, failed)` at the start (after its `_isAnalysisNotified(detailId, failed)` guard); pass **`failureDetail`** for errors
19. **`notifyReady` must guard at entry with `if (_isAnalysisNotified(detailId, failed)) return`** — the WS handler and the poll fallback can race; **`failed`** must participate in the key (`c:` vs `f:`) so a completion never suppresses a failure toast for the same `session_id`
20. **Processing cards must show skeleton shimmer, not placeholder text** — render `.skeleton-line.skeleton-title` / `.skeleton-line.skeleton-subtitle` when `status === 'processing'` and `job_title` / `company_name` are empty; never show `"Job Application"` / `"Company"` for a card that is still being analyzed
21. **`RES_3002` from `/workflow/start` must use a warning-style message** — duplicate job is not a server fault; mirror handling in `ui/src/pages/dashboard-new-application.ts` and `ui/src/shared/api.ts`
22. **`_submittedToastShownForSession` must dedupe "Application submitted!"** — one toast per `session_id` for the `agent_update` + new-card path; do not stack with the sessionStorage redirect toast
23. **Placeholder `company_name` values must not render as punctuation** — `—` / `-` / `N/A` from the LLM or DB are truthy strings; always normalize through **`isPlaceholderCompanyName()`** + **`displayCompanyNameOrUnknown()`** so users see **Unknown** (see **Unknown employer** section above)
24. **`syncProcessingApps` must pass `failed` into `_isAnalysisNotified` / `notifyReady`** — polling uses the same `c:` / `f:` keys as the WebSocket path; never call `_isAnalysisNotified(sessionId)` without the second argument on a terminal completion/failure path
